for parallax scrolling effect

Parallax scrolling is a web site trend where the background content (i.e. an image) is moved at a different speed than the foreground content while scrolling.

.parallax {
  /* The image used */
  background-image: url("img_parallax.jpg");

  /* Set a specific height */
  min-height: 500px; 

  /* Create the parallax scrolling effect */
  background-attachment: fixed;
  background-position: center;
  background-repeat: no-repeat;
  background-size: cover;


  // to center anything

      position: relative;
}

.center{
    position: absolute;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    top:50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%)  translateY(-50%);
    left:50%;
    color:white;
    background-color: black;
            
} 


use 
text-align,right-align,left-align... . to center your text.....

diffent properties for color
color,rgb(0,0,0);    0-255; 
hexadecimal -#FF0000  0-F; or
hexadecimal sort form -#F00; 
rgba(100,255,100,.5)  .5->50% transparent background or anything

use --->hsl->hue,saturation,lightness
hue->0-360 -->just find hue and adjust saturation and lightness..
50%-normal lightness no extraa black or no extraa light

hsla a->transparent.



// box-model
 margin,border,padding-->inside the content
 border:20px solid black
 border-width:10px 5px 2px 6px

 box-sizing:border-box -->it reduce the box size and add padding and border inside the box
 to make it that size which u tell to have.
 *{
     box-sizing:border-box..do it everytime/
 }

ivw=1percent
but percent depend upon screen size while vh and vw does not depend with parent.. only screen.


 1 rem--> root font size --> 16 px that never changes
 1 em-> based upon parent if parent has a 30px font size thenit became 
 1 em=30px;
